Document: NavigationObstacle2D
Path: godot/classes/class_navigationobstacle2d.rst
Summary: Defines a 2D obstacle for navigation avoidance.

NavigationObstacle2D is a node used to define obstacles in a navigation mesh. These obstacles are used by NavigationServer to avoid collisions with dynamic objects.

Inherits: Node2D < CanvasItem < Node < Object

Properties:
radius (float): The radius of the obstacle. This is used for circular obstacles. Default: 1.0.
width (float): The width of the obstacle. This is used for rectangular obstacles. Default: 1.0.
height (float): The height of the obstacle. This is used for rectangular obstacles. Default: 1.0.
obstacle_type (int): The type of the obstacle. Can be one of ObstacleType.BOX or ObstacleType.CYLINDER. Default: 0.
Use 3D extents for 3D obstacles.
obstacle_type: ObstacleType.BOX (0)
obstacle_type: ObstacleType.CYLINDER (1)
avoidance_layers (int): The avoidance layers the obstacle belongs to. Default: 1.
avoidance_mask (int): The avoidance layers the obstacle will avoid. Default: 4294967295.
use_rotation (bool): Whether to use the obstacle's rotation for avoidance. Default: true.
neighbor_distance (float): The distance to other obstacles to consider for avoidance. Default: 10.0.
neighbor_weight (float): The weight of the obstacle's influence on other obstacles. Default: 1.0.
obstacle_weight (float): The weight of the obstacle itself. Default: 1.0.
time_to_live (float): The time to live for the obstacle. If set to 0, the obstacle will live forever. Default: 0.0.

Methods:
set_avoidance_layers(layers: int)
Sets the avoidance layers the obstacle belongs to.

set_avoidance_mask(mask: int)
Sets the avoidance layers the obstacle will avoid.

set_neighbor_distance(distance: float)
Sets the distance to other obstacles to consider for avoidance.

set_neighbor_weight(weight: float)
Sets the weight of the obstacle's influence on other obstacles.

set_obstacle_weight(weight: float)
Sets the weight of the obstacle itself.

set_radius(radius: float)
Sets the radius of the obstacle.

set_time_to_live(time_to_live: float)
Sets the time to live for the obstacle.

set_use_rotation(use_rotation: bool)
Sets whether to use the obstacle's rotation for avoidance.

set_width(width: float)
Sets the width of the obstacle.

set_height(height: float)
Sets the height of the obstacle.

set_obstacle_type(type: int)
Sets the type of the obstacle.

get_avoidance_layers() → int
Returns the avoidance layers the obstacle belongs to.

get_avoidance_mask() → int
Returns the avoidance layers the obstacle will avoid.

get_neighbor_distance() → float
Returns the distance to other obstacles to consider for avoidance.

get_neighbor_weight() → float
Returns the weight of the obstacle's influence on other obstacles.

get_obstacle_weight() → float
Returns the weight of the obstacle itself.

get_radius() → float
Returns the radius of the obstacle.

get_time_to_live() → float
Returns the time to live for the obstacle.

get_use_rotation() → bool
Returns whether to use the obstacle's rotation for avoidance.

get_width() → float
Returns the width of the obstacle.

get_height() → float
Returns the height of the obstacle.

get_obstacle_type() → int
Returns the type of the obstacle.
