Document: NavigationObstacle2D
Path: godot/classes/class_navigationobstacle2d.rst
Summary: Defines the properties of a NavigationObstacle2D node, which affects navigation mesh generation and agent avoidance.

Properties
* affect_navigation_mesh (bool): If true, the obstacle will affect the navigation mesh by carving it or by being considered during its generation. Default: false.
* avoidance_enabled (bool): If true, the obstacle will be considered by agents using the navigation mesh for avoidance. Default: true.
* avoidance_layers (int): Bitmask of avoidance layers this obstacle belongs to. Agents will only avoid obstacles on layers they are configured to avoid. Default: 1.
* carve_navigation_mesh (bool): If true, the obstacle will carve a hole in the navigation mesh. This is only effective if affect_navigation_mesh is also true. Default: false.
* radius (float): The radius of the obstacle. Used for avoidance and for carving the navigation mesh if the obstacle is circular. Default: 0.0.
* velocity (Vector2): The current velocity of the obstacle. Used for avoidance calculations. Default: Vector2(0, 0).
* vertices (PackedVector2Array): The vertices of the obstacle's shape. Used for carving the navigation mesh if the obstacle is polygonal. Default: PackedVector2Array().
---CHUNK---
